Back at it...

Back trackside doing what I like most after the winter break. A bit of rust to knock off, but it's always very nice to kick off the new season in the warm Middle East.

Extremely happy and grateful to take on the challenge and join @drewgibsonphotography alongside @nickdunganphoto for the new @fiawec_official season around the world.
So nice and refreshing to visit new racetracks, shooting new cars and drivers with a team of superstars to work together with.

The Prologue at Sebring is over. Can't wait to get going with the race action in just a couple days time.

social_posts.post_text:
Le Mans.
I don’t even know where to start to describe how Le Mans centenary week was.
I never experienced such a crazy, hectic, disorganized, frustrating, demanding and draining event such as Le Mans. But it’s so incredible to see how many people from all over the world come together to make that amazing mess work.

I felt extremely privileged to cover the event for most prestigious manufacturers and teams for @drewgibsoncaptures alongside @nickdunganphoto 
I (almost) can’t wait already for the 2024 edition

social_posts.post_text:
Spa24h.
It was a very difficult week for many reasons, but it was all put very much in perspective when we were informed about the tragedy of Dilano van 't Hoff, on raceday.
Motorsport is dangerous and we all know that, but stuff like that just should not happen. It was tough to then try clear my mind and approach the race and work as I was supposed to.
